Nutrition Information for the Meal Plan

     * Calories 1570
     * Carbohydrate 176 g
     * Protein 94 g
     * Fat 58 g

     * Saturated Fat 12 g
     * Cholesterol 125 mg
     * Sodium 1840 mg
     * Dietary Fiber 37 g

   [mar2014-healthy-carb-diabetes.jpg]

Featured Cookbook

[16]The Healthy Carb Cookbook

   by Chef Jennifer Bucko, MCFE, & Lara Rondinelli, RD, LDN, CDE

   With diabetes, not only do you have to count the carbs you're eating;
   it’s also important that you are choosing healthy sources of
   carbohydrate. This unique cookbook with over 150 recipes shows you how
   to fit more fruits, vegetables, and other healthy carbohydrate sources
   into your meal plan without added fuss.

Featured Article

[17]Make Your Carbs Count!

   Having diabetes doesn’t mean you have to follow a low-carb diet or
   avoid carbohydrate foods.

